## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Solution using ***HashMap with sorting.***
- Here we store all same strings in a vector inside Hashmap.
- We’ll take every string from strs in temp then sort that by character. Push the main string to the map.
- Like these elements with the same character will push to the same vector of hashmap.
- Then push all the vectors from map to ans.
- **Time complexity:** O(n.klogk) /***k**\xA0is the length of string and\xA0**n**\xA0is the total no. of strings*

### Solution 02

- Solution using ***Map without sorting.***
- Here we’ll do the same but this time we’ll take a map of map to skip the sorting part.
- If we could use an unordered map then time complexity could reduce to O(nk), but as it takes O(logn) time for any operations, so time takes same as solution 1.
- Here we count the characters in map and push it to main map.
- **Time complexity:** O(n.klogk) /*insertion into a map takes **logK** time*

