# Explanation:

###### I have used double loop to check the maximum possible count of any slope with all combination of <B>i</B>th point.
- Return `size` if the vector's size is `less than` 3, i.e. 1 point will contain itself with a line & 2 points will make a line with their own pair.
- I've initialized a map `mp` inside the first loop, and it has a count of every slope that might possibly have an `i`th point and also handles the `self` point and `infinite slope` separately.
- After ending inside loop I have updated my final answer with `mx+self` points
- returned `ans`


#### Go through code once you will understand completely👇

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxPoints(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        int n =points.size();
        if(n<3)
        return n;

        int ans = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            unordered_map<double,int> mp;
            int self = 1;
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++){
                if(points[i][0] == points[j][0] && points[j][1] == points[i][1])
                self++;
                else if(points[i][0] == points[j][0])
                mp[INT_MAX]++;
                else{
                    double slope = double(points[i][1]-points[j][1])/double(points[i][0]-points[j][0]);
                    mp[slope]++;
                }
            }
            int mx = 0;
            for(auto ele : mp){
                mx = max(mx,ele.second);
            }
            ans = max(ans,mx+self);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
