# Intuition
Take a point and calculate slope between that point and other points. The slope may be infinite or finite.
Check for all the points and update answer as per the number of points with the same slope.

# Approach
Consider a map to store number of points with a given slope.
Take a varibale named infinite and increment it for the points whose slope is infinite, otherwise update map for non infinite slopes and update answer accordingly.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxPoints(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        if(points.size()<=2){return points.size();}//two or less points are always in a straight line
        int infinite=0;//to handle points with infinite slope
        int ans=0;//to store the number of maxpoints in a line
        double slope;

    for(int i=0;i<points.size()-1;i++){//iterating over points
        unordered_map<double,int> mp;//to store the occurance of a slope
        for(int j=i;j<points.size();j++){//checking slope of the point with other points

            if(points[j][0]==points[i][0]){//if x coordinates are same
