In this question we use the slope method of geometry
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Find the slope of every pair and store the number of pair for a particular slope using hash map.
2. Also check everytime if denominator is zero then assume the slope to be maximum value and store it. 
3. For every pair find the number of points whose slope is same and update the mx variable. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity : O(N^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity : O(N)
