* In this problem we have been asked about points on same line
* so we can use concept of slop here
* Let's see what is slop when two points are on same line:

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0c0cf5f3-2273-4b32-b4b7-137ca3054355_1673158155.5956109.png)

* Now if we assume that one other point that is b(x3, y3) that is also lies on this line, but when it should be true??
	* It can be on this line when line xy only``` if slop of xb == slop of xy```

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d8955fb8-4f94-404a-9e41-8e6b764fffb1_1673159850.7514677.png)




* Note
	* if there is only one pont then answer is 1
	* if there is only two points then one line can be drawn

So that's our intution
```
we will fix two points  and check for all other remaining points, is they are on same line or not
```

### Algorithm

```
n = points.size()
if(n <= 2) return n

ans = 2

for i = 0 to i < n
	for j = i+1 to j < n
		int curr = 2
		for k = 0 to k < n
			if k != i and k != j
				int x1 = points[i][0]
				int y1 = points[i][1]
				int x2 = points[j][0]
				int y2 = points[j][1]
				int x3 = points[k][0]
				int y3 = points[k][1]
				////for decimal comparion issue we are doing cross multiplication
				if((x2-x1)*(y3-y1) == (y2-y1)*(x3-x1))  
					curr = curr + 1
		ans = max(ans, curr)

return ans
```


### C++ Code

