solutions.content:
# Intro
In order to get the count of points on the same line we'll go through all points and compare them with the rest.
 - We'll refer to our point that will be compared to all others the **basePoint**
 - We'll every other point **secondPoint**

# How does it work?
 - in case the point is identical (same x and same y), then it's also on the same vertical, horizontal and the same slope.
 - remember when comparing to include the **basePoint** in your total, and include it **only once** in comparison 
 - for each basePoint create a Map to collect other points that lay on the same slope.
 - don't forget to reset the slopes map after each iteration.

# Big O
for each point in **N Points** you need to do **(N - 1) iterations ~= O(N)**
time: **O(N^2)**  
you need to create a map of worst case size O(N - 1) ~= O(N)
space: **O(N)** 

```
    public int maxPoints(Point[] points) {
        if (points.length < 2) return points.length;
        int maxPoints = 0;
        HashMap<Double,Integer> slopes = new HashMap<>();
        double slope;
        int horizontal, vertical, identical;
        int count;
        int basePoint = 1; // just helper to understand the code below
        for (Point base: points) {
          identical = 0;
          vertical = 0;
          horizontal = 0;
          for (Point second: points) {
              if (base == second) continue;
              // identical point
              if (base.x == second.x && base.y == second.y) {
                identical++; // remember identical is horiz. vertical. and same slope (count it in all cases)
              // on the same vertical line
              } else if (base.x == second.x) {
                vertical++;
              // on the same horizontal line
              } else if (base.y == second.y) {
                horizontal++;
              // on a specific slope
              } else {
                slope = (double)(base.x - second.x)/(base.y - second.y); // calculate the slope
                count = slopes.getOrDefault(slope, 0) + 1; // get old count in addition to this one
                slopes.put(slope, count); // save the new slope
                maxPoints = Math.max(maxPoints, count + basePoint + identical); // compare the count + the base point + all identicals
              }              
          }
          maxPoints = Math.max(maxPoints, basePoint + horizontal + identical); // compare all horiz. + all identicals
          maxPoints = Math.max(maxPoints, basePoint + vertical + identical); // compare all vert. + all identicals
          slopes.clear();
        }

        return maxPoints;
    }
```

