# Intuition
This question can be solved using mutliple ways such as map , set and two pointers.

# Approach
- sort both the vectors
- use two pointers ,for both the vectors
- increase second pointer if the element of first vector is greater
- increase first pointer if the element of second vector is greater
- if both the element are same and the result vector has not the same element then insert it into a result vector. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
  O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)


# Code
