### C++ solution in O(nlog(n)) time
The main idea behind this solution is to use binary search on previosly sorted array. What really makes this solution extremely fast is that after each iteration I am limit search space - I am increasing start_idx and I escape main loop when I see that furter search is unneccessary.

Algorithm:
1. If nums1 or nums2 is empty return empty array
2. Sort nums1 and nums2 using Quick Sort - O(nlog(n)) time complexity
3. Walk through the nums1 array and check whether current element from nums1 is in nums2
