**Solution 1: Using Two Sets**

Time complexity: `O(m + n)` -  where `m` and `n` are lengths of arrays.
Space complexity: `O(m + n)`

```
class Solution
{
    public int[] intersection(int[] A, int[] B)
	{
        Set<Integer> setA = new HashSet<>();
        Set<Integer> setAB = new HashSet<>();
		int i = 0;

        for(int n : A)
			setA.add(n);

        for(int n : B)
		{
            if(setA.contains(n))
			{
                setAB.add(n);
            }
        }

        int[] result = new int[setAB.size()];

		for(int n : setAB)
            result[i++] = n;

        return result;
    }
}
```

**Solution 2: Using Binary Search**

Time complexity: `O(m log n)`
Space complexity: `O(Min(m, n))`

```
class Solution
{
    public int[] intersection(int[] A, int[] B)
	{
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
		int i = 0;
		Arrays.sort(B);

		for(int n : A)
		{
            if(Arrays.binarySearch(B, n) >= 0)
			{
                set.add(n);
            }
        }

        int[] result = new int[set.size()];

		for (int n : set)
		{
            result[i++] = n;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
```

