BST is a special BT, so the solution of lc 297 can be directly applied to this problem. However, this problem asks us to encode the string as compact as possible. The BST property can be harnessed to save the null indicators that were used in lc 297. The following solution is adapted from [this post](https://discuss.leetcode.com/topic/66450/python-o-n-solution-easy-to-understand) with some modifications. 

```
class Codec:

    def serialize(self, root):
        vals = []
        self._preorder(root, vals)
        return ','.join(vals)

    def _preorder(self, node, vals):
        if node:
            vals.append(str(node.val))
            self._preorder(node.left, vals)
            self._preorder(node.right, vals)

    def deserialize(self, data):
        vals = collections.deque(map(int, data.split(','))) if data else []
        return self._build(vals, -float('inf'), float('inf'))

    def _build(self, vals, minVal, maxVal):
        if vals and minVal < vals[0] < maxVal:
            val = vals.popleft()
            root = TreeNode(val)
            root.left = self._build(vals, minVal, val)
            root.right = self._build(vals, val, maxVal)
            return root
        else:
            return None
```

